            <h2 style="color:black; text-align:left"> <b>About the Ecuador</b></h2>
            <p>
                Ecuador is a truly authentic adventure for nature lovers. It is the most biodiverse country
                in the world per square kilometer where in short distances you find different ecosystems like
                glaciers, deserts, moorland highlands, deep scrublands, cloud forests, the Amazon Rainforest
                and palm tree-lined beaches where the water is crystal clear.
            </p>
            <p>
                Ecuador is the perfect destination to discover something genuine, unique and surprising. Ideal
                if you want to avoid spending your holiday in crowded places. It is one of the few destinations
                in the world that can still surprise the most demanding traveler.
            </p>
            <p>
                If you want to learn about different cultures, in Ecuador you can find 11 indigenous nations
                that still preserve their traditions. You can learn from interaction with them through shared
                experiences, workshops, and through their gastronomy.
            </p>
            <p id="resources">
                Also, two cities in the country were named World Heritage Sites by UNESCO: Quito and Cuenca.
            </p>
