            <h2 style="color:black; text-align:left; margin-top:3%"> <b>Regions of Mainland Ecuador</b></h2>
            <p>
                The mainland is divided into three regions; Coast, Andes and Amazon Rainforests.
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>Andes: </b>The cultural and natural diversity encompasses moorland highlands,
                cloud forests, mountain lakes, active volcanoes, thermal baths, indigenous markets,
                colonial villages and haciendas.
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>Amazon: </b>This region is home to 20% of the planet's biodiversity and is one of
                the places that did not freeze during the last ice age. In the Ecuadorian Amazon you
                can find more species of animals and plants per square hectare than in all of Europe
                and North America combined.
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>Coat: </b>Located on the western side of Ecuador and spreading along the Pacific,
                this region has a number of beautiful beaches and is home to Ecuador's largest city
                and main ports, as well as many communities of artisans and fishermen.
            </p>
